description:
**A Tribo**


'Prozis is a powerhouse product developing company. Every day we make new products. That is only possible because we developed our own proprietary technology that ensures that we bring you high quality, beautiful and fair priced products. We endure in our philosophy of a 4\\.0 vertical process, manufacturing in our own facilities or with the help of our superpartners. We do everything: idea, concept, design, manufacturing, quality control, marketing, sales, logistics, printing, distribution, client support, software development, photo, video, 3D and philosophy. We deliver wherever you are, whenever you want. We don't compromise. We breathe technology, drink design and feed on our will to exceed ourselves making the best products in the world. This all starts in 2007 with a crazy guy in a garage that thinks he can change the world for the better. Right now, we are hundreds, going to thousands of crazy but focused people. Will is a skill. There is a lot of people that want to buy us out. We don't have a F\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\* price tag. It's not about the money. It's about our mission. Trust us. We will feed your body and mind with everything you need to exceed yourself.'


* miguel milhão



**A Equipa**


Movidos pelo mesmo propósito, entregar valor aos nossos clientes, todos os dias encaramos os desafios com rigor, compromisso, sentido de ação e aquela vontade que só quem nos conhece entende. Criamos, Desenvolvemos, Produzimos e Entregamos, acreditando que não existem limites para a nossa ambição. Com uma vasta experiência no setor têxtil, esta equipa tem como cartão de visita o conhecimento, a inovação, o desenvolvimento, a excelência e a paixão em tudo o que entrega.


**As Pessoas que procuramos**


Na Prozis, “will is a skill”. Não procuramos competência sem motivação, nem motivação sem superação e perseverança. Identificas\\-te com este ADN? Então dá uma vista de olhos na oportunidade que temos especialmente para ti:





**A Função**


* Executar os projetos de amostra desenvolvidos pela equipa de desenho criativo;
* Programar os desenhos nos equipamentos (Lonati);
* Manutenção dos equipamentos e respetiva parametrização de acordo com o produto pretendido;
* Participar na seleção da matéria\\-prima (fios) das peças em desenvolvimento;
* Acompanhar a passagem do processo de amostra para produção em escala;
* Garantir os parâmetros de qualidade definidos pela empresa.


**Tu**


* Experiência na produção de Amostras de Meias/Peúgas;
* Conhecimentos sólidos de Teares Circulares (Lonati);
* Conhecimentos de matéria\\-prima.


**Os teus superpoderes**


* Desenvoltura e rápida capacidade de adaptação;
* Proatividade;
* Boa comunicação interpessoal;
* Capacidade para trabalhar em equipa;
* Espírito crítico;
* Resiliência;
* Planeamento e organização.





Reúnes o que que é preciso para nos ajudares nesta nova aventura?


Não percas tempo, envia\\-nos a tua candidatura.





**Sabias que...**


Temos mais de 10 fábricas?


Btw: A Prozis não é para todos!


*Nos termos da Política de Recrutamento do grupo PROZIS, a pessoa portadora de deficiência, nos termos da Lei n.º 38/2004, de 18/08, cuja candidatura não tenha sido admitida ou respondida no prazo de 30 dias, tem a faculdade de pedir a fundamentação da decisão e a sua reavaliação através de pedido apresentado no canal de denúncias constante de www.prozis.com, na categoria 'direitos e protecção dos indivíduos'.*

**A Tribo**


"Prozis is a powerhouse product developing company. Every day we make new products. That is only possible because we developed our own proprietary technology that ensures that we bring you high quality, beautiful and fair priced products. We endure in our philosophy of a 4\\.0 vertical process, manufacturing in our own facilities or with the help of our superpartners. We do everything: idea, concept, design, manufacturing, quality control, marketing, sales, logistics, printing, distribution, client support, software development, photo, video, 3D and philosophy. We deliver wherever you are, whenever you want. We don't compromise. We breathe technology, drink design and feed on our will to exceed ourselves making the best products in the world. This all starts in 2007 with a crazy guy in a garage that thinks he can change the world for the better. Right now, we are hundreds, going to thousands of crazy but focused people. Will is a skill. There is a lot of people that want to buy us out. We don't have a F\\*\\*\\*\\*\\*\\* price tag. It's not about the money. It's about our mission. Trust us. We will feed your body and mind with everything you need to exceed yourself."


* miguel milhão


**A Equipa**


Continuando a expansão das áreas de negócio a que se propôs, a Prozis está focada em investir em diferentes processos produtivos. Com toda a paixão que já nos caracteriza, esta equipa está concentrada na produção de embalagens plásticas, trabalhando para o desenvolvimento de produtos de excelência no mercado.


**A Função**


Este profissional vem integrar uma equipa jovem e ambiciosa, e vai ajudar a "moldar" mais um projeto arrojado, assumindo as seguintes responsabilidades:


* Gestão de toda a operação da máquina de injeção, desde a preparação da matéria\\-prima, até à fase de acabamentos, respeitando as especificações da área alimentar;
* Operacionalização do equipamento produtivo;
* Consolidar a expedição do produto acabado;


**Tu**


* Conhecimentos informáticos na ótica do utilizador (utilizador básico);
* Experiência mínima de 1 ano na área de automação industrial, ou similar (preferencial);
* Conhecimentos práticos de instrumentação, motores elétricos, pneumática, processos e equipamentos de produção;
* Conhecimentos básicos para proceder à afinação de equipamentos;
* Disponibilidade para trabalhar em horários rotativos (laboração contínua).


**Os teus superpoderes**


* Desenvoltura e rápida capacidade de adaptação;
* Flexibilidade e disponibilidade;
* Boa comunicação interpessoal;
* Capacidade para trabalhar em equipa;
* Espírito crítico;
* Planeamento e organização.


Reúnes o que que é preciso para nos ajudares a “moldar” este novo desafio?


Não percas tempo, envia\\-nos a tua candidatura.



**Sabias que...**


Temos mais de 12 fábricas?

**Join Us**
-----------



At Vodafone, we’re not just shaping the future of connectivity for our customers – we’re shaping the future for everyone who joins our team. When you work with us, you’re part of a global mission to connect people, solve complex challenges, and create a sustainable and more inclusive world. If you want to grow your career whilst finding the perfect balance between work and life, Vodafone offers the opportunities to help you belong and make a real impact.

**What you’ll do**
------------------


* Define, align and maintain the technology strategy for the Product Integration Platform Ability to interpret business challenges and technical issues and effectively communicate how a solution will align to their needs and requirements;
* Drives understanding of the big picture. Works in close cooperation with Technical and Commercial Product Owners, Vodafone Enterprise, local markets and partners; leading to the Technology strategy, High\\-Level Design and contributing to shared propositions;
* Enable solution opportunities by identifying the requirements directly from the Vodafone local markets/Partner markets or by proactively understanding their needs. Able to express complex concepts in plain language to reach broader audiences;
* Delivery of products and services \\- lead the design and delivery of respective portfolio as aligned with Group Commercial, local markets and partners;
* This design includes: Interfaces specification (APIs) Infrastructure architecture Software architecture Security design Data models and analytics requirements Connectivity to other services enablers System management specific requirements and integration Technical expert contribution to the technology selection process and make or buy decisions in synchronization with Technology standards;
* Represent Vodafone in standardisation and other industry forums regarding APIs.
**Who you are**
---------------


* Technical degree level (MSc) Extensive experience in designing complex, distributed, secure and scalable architecture solutions Excellent Knowledge of enterprise solutions and architectures (cloud, big data, security, containerization, storage);
* Strong knowledge of architecture best practices and design patterns \\- Micro\\-Services (or Self\\-ContainedServices);
* API definition (Rest/SOAP/GraphQL) and API integration open programmes (including provisioning, login, charging and transaction); Security; Scalability; Cloud Services (K8s, AWS);
* Proven experience of conducting technical workshop, presenting technical solutions, preparing architecture guidelines and technical strategy documents;
* Familiar with design and development tools, and capable of suggesting new tools/process;
* Passionate about simple and clean SW architectures;
* Should have a very good analytical, consultative and problem\\-solving mind\\-set, and an influential personality capable of quickly building rapport and credibility with teams
* Excellent communication skills (in an international distributed team);
* Background in software development;
* Capacity to learn and work independently;
* Related qualification and proven experience in mobile technology, digital products or IT Knowledge of authentication technologies/protocols (SSO, oAuth2\\.0, Token management);
* Knowledge of web\\-based and service based architectures;
* Knowledge of web security standards and of cross platform architecture, technology and platforms Experienced in design and development of highly scalable, robust, efficient, distributed systems;
* Experience in application architecture and hands\\-on development Experience in agile development/SCRUM and continuous delivery processes.
**Not a perfect fit?**
----------------------



Worried that you don’t meet all the desired criteria exactly? At Vodafone we are passionate about empowering people and creating a workplace where everyone can thrive, whatever their personal or professional background. If you’re excited about this role but your experience doesn’t align exactly with every part of the job description, we encourage you to still apply as you may be the right candidate for this role or another opportunity.

**What's in it for you**
------------------------


* The Product Integration Platform function within Digital Engineering is a service provider for containerized cloud and API gateways, as well as software delivery and lifecycle (APIs, microservices, ...) for Vodafone products and services, and beyond. And it is owning the Product Integration Platform that is enabling, orchestrating and exposing Markets and Group capabilities to third parties and Vodafone services.
* The PIP consists of the API exposure layer, the Global Integration Gateway, lots of micro services, Websub (PubSub) and AAA (Authentication, Authorization, Accounts), mostly based on the K8s based CaaS (Container as a Service) capabilitiy.
* The Product Integration Platform function is accountable for architecture design, development, deployment and operations of state\\-of\\-the\\-art propositions in the API and integration space.
* By using the latest technologies and agile delivery practices, all these APIs and platforms are provided with high  

quality to ensure excellent brand and revenue impact on 150 third parties in more than 20 markets are contributing  

to more than 800m€ gross revenue p.a with 3000TPS in peak.
* The purpose of this role is to define and lead the overall architecture strategy and roadmap for all aspects of the Product Integration Platform. The architecture will be developed to provide innovative solutions that meet the market and global business requirements, whilst ensuring compliance with the architecture standards and design principles. Part of this role is also to contribute and enhance the architecture standard where applicable and to show disruptive ways proving to be successful.  

The role incumbent should as well be able to guide developers using the appropriate design patterns and best practices and even to demonstrate them.
* The Principal Architect will lead the architecture domain in the Product Integration Platform function and provides guidelines, direction, mentorship and expert support to several senior architects, developers and technical experts that work in the different projects. As the lead technical representative for Product Integration Platform, it is vital to stay connected inside and outside the Vodafone Technology community, with industry experts to understand the latest technology trends and drive innovative solutions. Strong analytical, functional, technical and communication skills are imperative for this role. The role will also lead the governance and evolution of the platforms and API strategy.
* The Principal Architect owns the governance in respect of API architecture when working with Distinguished  

Engineers, other Principal Architects and other technical expert stakeholders.
**Who we are**
--------------



We are a leading international Telco, serving millions of customers. At Vodafone, we believe that connectivity is a force for good. If we use it for the things that really matter, it can improve people's lives and the world around us. Through our technology we empower people, connecting everyone regardless of who they are or where they live and we protect the planet, whilst helping our customers do the same.


Belonging at Vodafone isn't a concept; it's lived, breathed, and cultivated through everything we do. You'll be part of a global and diverse community, with many different minds, abilities, backgrounds and cultures. ;We're committed to increase diversity, ensure equal representation, and make Vodafone a place everyone feels safe, valued and included.


If you require any reasonable adjustments or have an accessibility request as part of your recruitment journey, for example, extended time or breaks in between online assessments, please refer to https://careers.vodafone.com/application\\-adjustments/ for guidance.


Together we can.

**Position: Functional Analyst**  

**Location: Remote from Portugal**

##### **Who We Are**


At Nimber, were more than just a growing team were building a collective of professionals ready to challenge convention, innovate with purpose, and deliver real value to our clients. We dont believe in coincidences. If this role caught your attention, it might just be the opportunity you were meant to find.

##### **What Were Looking For**


We are seeking a highly analytical, structured, and motivated Functional Analyst with a strong ability to interpret, conceptualise and design complex information flows and technical solutions. The ideal candidate will combine skills in functional analysis, software development, and data modelling, acting as a vital bridge between business vision and technical implementation.

##### **Key Responsibilities**

* Conduct detailed functional analysis based on business and regulatory requirements;
* Design and document information flows, algorithms, and data models;
* Translate business needs into clear, structured technical and functional specifications;
* Contribute to architectural discussions, with a strong focus on data structuring and API design;
* Evaluate the technical feasibility and scope of new features and support backlog grooming and sprint planning;
* Collaborate with Product Owners, Developers, and Business Stakeholders to align on solution design and delivery;
* Support development teams throughout implementation, ensuring adherence to best engineering practices;
* Promote a culture of technical excellence, continuous improvement, and scalability.

##### **Requirements**

* University degree in Computer Engineering, Physics Engineering, Civil Engineering, or related technical fields;
* Minimum of 3 years of experience as a Functional Analyst, Business Analyst, or Product Owner (experience in SaaS or complex software products is a plus);
* Strong analytical and system\\-thinking skills, with fluency in data structures, process modelling and algorithmic thinking;
* Proven experience in designing technical specifications, APIs, and data models;
* Ability to clearly communicate technical concepts to non\\-technical stakeholders;
* Familiarity with Agile methodologies (Scrum or Kanban);
* Fluent in both Portuguese and English (written and spoken).

##### **Nice to Have**

* Experience with middleware platforms (e.g., Strapi) or event\\-driven architectures;
* Knowledge of data architecture, analytical pipelines, or scalable systems;
* Background or interest in construction, civil engineering, or infrastructure sectors.

##### **Why Join Nimber?**


At Nimber, we believe in fairness, independence, and real impact. We value those who think differently, challenge assumptions, and strive to create meaningful change through technology. If you're seeking more than just a job if you want to be part of something that matters this might be the place for you.

**Tired of being just another number?**  

Become a Nimber. Apply now.

